message.content:
A digital watch is an electronic timepiece that displays the time in numerical digits. 
It features a screen that typically has a black background with brightly lit numbers. 
The digits on a digital watch are usually of a uniform size and shape. 
It may be made out of various materials, such as plastic, stainless steel, or silicone. 
Digital watches are commonly used for sports activities or everyday wear. 
They may have additional features, such as alarms, stopwatches, or timers. 
Digital watches have become increasingly popular since their introduction in the 1970s.
